Text.string: Atlas, huh? We'll have to convince them to help us find the Vault before the Calypsos do. Killer, plug in that astronav chip so we can set a course for Promethea.
As Mega-General Admiral of the Crimson Raiders, I demand the honor of plugging in the astronav chip!
What in the HELL?!
That's weird. I'm not showing that hull breach anymore!
Is there anyone there? Hello? Follow the clinical sound of my voice!
Vault Hunter, can you... hear me?
Uh, where you at, Tannis?
Uh, where are you, Tannis?
Tannis. Where are you?
Tannis? We playing hide and seek?
Such curious internal organs.
A double-lacerating jaw, fascinating.
It smells like my first day of school in here.
Well, I suppose this is technically a micro-climate. Hahaha!
Ah! Good. Be with you in just a moment.
Ah, crap. No prob, lemme just turn on the fire suppressant system.
Damn, looks like someone used up all the cryo tanks! We got no pressure!
Cargo bay is re-pressurized. Earl's storage closet is just over yonder.
Stubborn thing's jammed, huh? See if you can make it budge.
Everyone all right?
Earl, wake the hell up! Our ship's dead in the water and we need your help!
Whatchu want?
Earl, it's been a day, amigo. Don't test me.
I need some Eridium. This my lucky day?
I'm looking for Eridium. Got any?
I require Eridium. Do you have any?
I see how it is. Oh, right. I need some, ehhh... Eridium, or something. Got some?
All right, all right, just trying to be hospitable.
What? Nothin' strike yer fancy? Well, I'm tired of looking at ya! Scram!
Wow! They have more followers than ME! Maybe I should make my own propaganda videos!
You can have the damn hooza-whatsit.
[assortment of sounds of people partying and drinking]
Come back never.
We got a hull breach! Pressure's falling!
Come on...
What's happening? I can't see! I can't see!
Here we go!
Claptrap, what intel do we have on Promethea?
Ahh, Promethea! A shining metropolis and the home of the Atlas Corporation! It's the most technologically-advanced planet in this arm of the galaxy!
Oh, I just assumed that installing the astronav was beneath someone of your stature.
Hey, you're right! This is a task for the lowest-ranking crewmember! Recruit, install that astronav chip!
Uh, I think we lost gravity!
Uh, are we supposed to be floating?
So I'm floating now. How novel.
Ha-HA! I'm bloody flying!
Claptrap... keep your ass in that hole.
What the hell is going on?
You can count on me!
Thanks! But my firing range is still on fire!
Yay!
Ugh, that room smelled like farts!
Let's get outta here!
My bladder is gonna explode!
That robot is evil! Evil!
We need a freakin' union!
Hell yeah! Sweet, sweet freedom!
Yes! That's what I'm talkin' about!
Hnh... aghh... whoa-whoa! Aaagh!
All right! Thanks, Vault Hunter!
You ain't got squat—no sale!

Earl, you—rgh! Vault Hunter, he's locked in there tight. Maybe if you had some more Eridium, he'd be willin' to trade. Go talk to my mama at the bar. She keeps all kinds of currency around just in case.
See anything you like?
You got Eridium? Gooooood! You can have that... what's-it-called thingy, if you buy somethin'.
Terrible doing business with you, Earl.

Hey, Lil, you're back on the grid! Thought you might have just, y'know—chk-chk, thbwthbw! Heh.||While you were gone, Troy whipped up a propaganda vid for our followers. Galaxy premiere! Check it out. You're a star!
Lookin' good, Liarhawk!
Better hurry up and get to Promethea! See you later, have a good war!
Say what you will about those guys, but their production value is through the roof!
Ughhhh... my exhaust port...
Here we go.
What the hell? That's a Maliwan fleet!
I thought this was an Atlas planet. Somethin' ain't right, Lil.
If you got business to attend to on Pandora, I suggest you take care of it now. Otherwise, on the ship, VH.
Lil... what the hell happened to you?
Her tattoos are gone. Lilith is... no longer a Siren.
You're sayin' Tyreen stole Lil's powers? Well, let's hunt down that god-queen-bitch and get 'em right back!
Are you crazy?! I say we stay here and build a fort!
Tyreen's after the power of the Vault, and there's no one else who can stop her. We have to get there first. I may not be a Siren, but I'm still a Crimson Raider. We all are.
Damn it. The drive's busted! Nav and propulsion too.
Hey, Lil. Bad luck to take a ship out of orbit without a name.
She's already got a name. Sanctuary.
Vault Hunter. Over here.
Tannis isn't wrong. Tyreen is more dangerous than ever. She's got an army, the map, and... my Siren powers. We're gonna need all the help we can get.
To Claptrap's point. Can we really take on the Calypsos in our current... state?
I'm with you, Lil, through thick and thin. You know which one's which, stringbean.
We're back online, Lil!
Certain death it is! And I obviously won't pass up a chance to study a new Vault.
That's what I've been saying!
All right. Let's get to it.
Astronav is installed, Lil. We're good to go.
A quick systems check, and we're ready to get out of here.
Not my kind of flying. Glad that's over.
That's because the only thing standing between this ship and space is my ass! MY ass saved all YOUR asses!
All right. Let's get the hell out of here.
Well, we arrived in one piece. That's a first.
Until we get our systems online, we're dead in the sky. Ellie, how long's that gonna take?
Keep your skinny pants on, Lil. I'm working on it!
Do what you can. Fast.
Vault Hunter, go check on the rest of the crew. See if anyone needs help.
My wares! My beautiful implements of destruction! Vault Hunter, quick, do something!
Despite what my advertisements say, you can't fight fire with fire!
Could you shoot those cryo release valves?
Fire on a firing range? Who could have seen that coming?
Shoot the cryo release valve, Vault Hunter.
I appreciate the help, Vault Hunter. But don't expect a fire sale.
Don't worry about me, I'm all right—just staying warm! The thermal control system malfunctioned during the hull breach. You'll need to reboot it.
We ride! Onward, to Promethea!
Just a moment!||Almost there...||Nghh... rgh...||Rgh! Whew! Surprisingly comfortable, you know. Like a fleshy sleeping bag. Although I do feel a bit... viscous.
Thank you for bringing my lab back to a survivable temperature. You should go see if anyone else requires assistance. I will contact you if any other devices require... punching.
We're trapped!
Help!
Anyone out there? Let us out!
That maniac locked us in here!
Those doors should be working fine. Someone locked those poor bastards in before takeoff! Get 'em out of there, VH.
We're saved!
That robot is insane!
Go ahead and install that astronav chip, VH!
Shut up, he said he'd punish us if we told anyone.
Claptrap, did you imprison our crew?
You mean the intergalactic interns/slaves?! Of course! I locked them all in a small room to ensure their unwavering loyalty. It's Management 101!
I'm going to say this once: no slaves.
No slaves for a week. Got it!
Recruit. Since I can't use my prison cells anymore, I guess you can use one as your personal bunk!
Nice goin', Vault Hunter! I found the problem. Blown entropy accelerator. I got a spare one in the cargo bay. Come help me out, will ya?
Blown entropy accelerator ain't no thang. Got loads of spare parts in the cargo bay—and some special gear I was saving for ya!
Aw hell. We gotta cut our losses and vent the cargo bay!

Well, there goes the grapple-grabber, the jetpack, and all the left-handed guns... guess it wasn't meant to be. But if Earl didn't get sucked out into the icy maw of space, he should have a spare entropy accelerator.
All right, Lil. We're good to go!
Earl, you damn stowaway! What the hell are you doing?
I'm busy. Now scram!
I trust you, Ellie.
Just hand over the entropy accelerator, Earl.
I don't see your name on the door! Whatever yer name is.
Hand over that part, or I'ma twist ya into a pretzel and fondue your ass.
Fair enough. I'd give it to ya if ya had somethin' worth my while, but ya don't! So get lost, freeloader!

Trust has nothin' to do with it, Lil! Firing up the generators. Rerouting the subharmonic geller oscilator to point-two. Lil, activate the implosion drive manifold bearing to eighty by one thirty-nine.
Got it... uh, wait, Ellie—where's the whatever you just said?
Someone help me! My totally legitimate business is on fire!
Brace yerselves. This baby's sportin' an implosion drive. That means you gotta be REAL careful with it. A single miscalculation could end this adventure real quick.
Thanks for saving my ass, Vault Hunter.
Thanks. Come on back and let's have a little... chat.
However, you can take an SDU from your old pal Marcus. The more you can carry, the more you can buy from me!
Not bad!
That one could be useful.
That could say your life one day.
That will come in handy. Trust old Marcus.
Pleasure doing business with you, Vault Hunter.
The name's Moxxi. What's yours, sugar?
Moze. And you look like trouble.
I'm Amara. And you're a knock-out.
I am FL4K, and your pheromones are... overwhelming.
Uhh. It's Zane? We had a weekend at the casino? Did you forget me?
Boring! I got this! Onward to Promethea!
[flirty chuckle] Guilty as charged.
Nothing today? Well, come back anytime.

I remember when I was in your position! The lowest rung of the ladder, hardly better than a dusty turd! So, I left a few pieces of garbage-slash-decorations to make your tiny, insignificant room feel more like your own!
Quit thirstin' up our new Vault Hunter, Ma, we're in the crap. We need some Eridium to fix the ship.
Have you tried my slots? Maybe you'll get lucky.
Well, would you look at that. You've got the magic touch.
Come back any time, sugar. I've got a few other games we could play.
All right, VH, go give that turd blossom Earl what he wants.
That so hard?
Well, that was a bitch and a half. Now go install that new entropy accelerator! We gotta get a move on!
Claptrap, wait!
Aw yeah. She's purrin' like a skag with a belly full of bandit. We're back online, Lil.
Ignore them—we've got work to do. Vault Hunter, let's get out of here—for real this time. Take us to Promethea.
Hold onto your cheeks, y'all. This one's gonna burn!
My cheeks are the only thing keeping you ungrateful air-breathers alive!
My ass... it's full of stars!
Enjoy, recruit! Maybe I'll come by and admire/judge your room's feng shui later!
An entropy accelerator.
An entropy accelerator.
An entropy accelerator.
An entropy accelerator.
Looks like we aren't the only ones with their eye on Promethea. Vault Hunter, over here.
Listen. About what happened on Pandora.
We can't let anything slow us down. You're gonna have to pick up the slack for me. Can I count on you?
Head to the bridge, VH. Let's get outta here!
Oh, I got this, Commander.
Yes, Commander. We are a pack now.
I got your back, Commander.
On it, Commander.
Good. Now, let's make contact with Atlas. If anyone knows where the Vault is, it's them.
Ellie, what's your status?
Cargo bay's looking damn fine, Lil!
Tannis, how's the lab?
I am surrounded by syringes and specimens. It feels like home.
Got it. Marcus?
Marcus Munitions' newest location is open and ready for profiteering... I mean, business, heh-heh!
Claptrap—what did you do?
One sec, y'all. I'll reboot the grav generator.
